byline.original: By PATRICK HEALY and YAMICHE ALCINDOR

abstract: Hillary Clinton turns her presidential campaign's attention to New York, painting herself as hometown candidate in state she represented in United States Senate for eight years; defeat in New York at hands of Bernie Sanders would prove humiliating for Clinton.
lead_paragraph: In a forceful opening bid to win New York, which she represented in the United States Senate for eight years, Mrs. Clinton presented herself as the quintessential hometown candidate.

headline.main: Shifting From Wisconsin, Hillary Clinton Tells New Yorkers That She’s One of Them
